@page "/breadcrumb"

<Content Title="Breadcrumb">
    The Bulma breadcrumb is a simple navigation component that only requires 
    a <code>breadcrumb</code> container and a list of items. 
    The dividers are automatically created.

    You can inform the current page by setting the IsActive property in
    <code>BreadcrumbItem</code> class to <code>true</code>. 
    It will disable the navigation of inner links
</Content>

<Snippet IsVertical=true>
    <Output>
        <Breadcrumb Items=@Items ></Breadcrumb> 
    </Output>
    <Code>
@("<Breadcrumb Items=@Items ></Breadcrumb> ")
@("@code {")
    @("IEnumerable<BreadcrumbItem> Items = new List<BreadcrumbItem> {") 
        @("new BreadcrumbItem { Text=\"Home\", Link=\"/\" },")
        @("new BreadcrumbItem { Text=\"Component\", Link=\"/\" },")
        @("new BreadcrumbItem { Text=\"Breadcrumb\", Link=\"/breadcrumb\", IsActive=true }")
    @("};")
@("}")
    </Code>
</Snippet>


@code 
{
    IEnumerable<BreadcrumbItem> Items = new List<BreadcrumbItem> {
    new BreadcrumbItem { Text="Home", Link="/" },
    new BreadcrumbItem { Text="Component", Link="/" },
    new BreadcrumbItem { Text="Breadcrumb", Link="/breadcrumb", IsActive=true }
    };
}